{
  "texts": [
    "Both models showed better performance with the E+G predictor compared to the G predictor in two out of three environments in terms of NRMSE.",
    "However, the results were opposite in terms of Cor, where the G predictor exhibited better performance in the other two environments.",
    "In this case, the DL model outperformed the GBLUP Pearson's correlation obtained in each environment when applying LOEO strategy for each of the five traits (Germination, Heading, Height, Maturity, and Yield) for GBLUP and multi-modal deep learning (DL) models using two predictors (G and E+G).",
    "Normalized mean squared error (NRMSE) obtained in each environment when applying LOEO strategy for each of the five traits (Germination, Heading, Height, Maturity, and Yield) for GBLUP and multi-modal deep learning (DL) models using two predictors (G and E+G).",
    "model in the BDRT environment for both NRMSE and Cor metrics, and in the remaining two environments the GBLUP was better."
  ]
}